HEADWORD: Plethysmography
<hw>Pleth`ys*mog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The study, by means of the plethysmograph, of
the variations in size of a limb, and hence of its blood
supply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

